Name: Hydrothermal Fuel Cell
Description:
A high thermal energy fuel, contained within a standardised fuel cell. Used to fuel the Humboldt Drive that powers the Nautilon submarine.

Created with a mix of organic compounds (Carbon and cyto-phosphates) and localised mineral salts.

Name: Memory Fragment (exocraft)
Description:
The shattered remnants of a previous existence. It whispers, an unknowable name deep within its fibres.

The memory will manifest as an Exocraft upgrade to aid you in this iteration. Absorb this memory with [E].

Name: Flatbed Chassis Module
Description:
A custom body module for a terrestrial vehicle, compatible with the Colossus large Exocraft.

The Flatbed Module allows the Colossus to haul heavy stacks of industrial waste across long distances. An electromagnetic containment field minimises cargo loss while navigating uneven terrain.

Recalibrate Exocraft visuals from the Colossus Geobay.

Description:

Name: Exocraft Summoning Unit
Description:
A high-powered matter teleportation device, this personal translocator allows any connected Exocraft to be instantly transported to your location, from anywhere in the galaxy.

Interfaces with the Exosuit Quick Menu for ease of use.

Name: Fusion Engine
Description:
A compact fusion core common to all Exocraft.

Requires fuel to function.

Name: Drift Suspension
Description:
Overhauls Exocraft handling values through a combination of software tweaks, pressure adjustments and the insertion of microgravity wells into key suspension components.

Specifically tuned to increase the ability of the Exocraft to drift.

Name: Grip Boost Suspension
Description:
Overhauls Exocraft handling values through a combination of software tweaks, pressure adjustments and the insertion of microgravity wells into key suspension components.

Specifically tuned to increase the ability of the Exocraft to turn sharply.

Name: Hi-slide Suspension
Description:
Overhauls Exocraft handling values through a combination of software tweaks, pressure adjustments and the insertion of microgravity wells into key suspension components.

Specifically tuned to increase the ability of the Exocraft to slide.

Name: Thermal Buffer
Description:
Sublimation cooling vents and high-thermal mass buffers are installed in all structural panels, keeping the Exocraft pilot at non-lethal temperatures even in the most overwhelming of firestorms.

Entirely prevents all damage or energy drain while inside an Exocraft in scorched environments.

Name: Megawatt Heater
Description:
Installs a powerful heater into the Exocraft, keeping the cabin a habitable temperature even in the most freezing of conditions.

Entirely prevents all damage or energy drain while inside an Exocraft in freezing environments.

Name: Air Filtration Unit
Description:
Double-vacuumed air filtration systems allow no trace of the planetary atmosphere into the Exocraft cabin without being thoroughly scrubbed.

Entirely prevents all damage or energy drain while inside an Exocraft in toxic environments.

Name: Neutron Shielding
Description:
Highly-efficient control materials are inserted into the frame of the Exocraft, neutralising dangerous incoming energy waves.

Entirely prevents all damage or energy drain while inside an Exocraft in radioactive environments.

Name: Excavation Blade
Description:
A obstacle demolition attachment for a terrestrial vehicle, compatible with the Colossus large Exocraft.

The Excavation Blade allows the Colossus to collect a small number of resources from minerals and vegetation upon collision, and reduces grime and scratches to the Exocraft's paintwork.

Name: Exocraft Radar
Description:
A large and complex field-based subspace radar.

Due to its large power consumption and inherent subatomic instability, this technology must be mounted to an Exocraft.

Press QUICK_MENU to activate the Signal Booster.

Name: Cyclops Scope
Description:
An enhancement to the Exocraft's navigational capabilities, attaching to the driver's visor display. Analyses surroundings and projects detailed data over the environment, identifying points of interest and generating valuable data when used to study flora, fauna and minerals.

Hold AIM to operate.

Name: Exocraft Mining Laser
Description: A powerful mining laser, too cumbersome for handheld operation. Allows the Exocraft to extract naturally-occuring substances from organic or geological objects.

Name: Mounted Cannon
Description: Due to the energy requirements of this powerful weapon, they can only be fired from an Exocraft mount.

Name: Mounted Flamethrower
Description:
A mounted flamethrower specifically designed for the Exocraft. Causes extreme damage at close range.

Use CYCLEWEAPON to cycle available weapon modes.

Name: Humboldt Drive
Description:
A thermally-efficient, inversion-proof reactor engine capable of powering the Nautilon even at extreme depths.

Powered by Hydrothermal Fuel Cells.

Name: Nautilon Cannon
Description:
A mounted cannon specifically designed for the Nautilon Submarine.

A high-energy weapon system, it superheats a small body of water before launching it rapidly towards the intended target.

Designed primarily for damage against biological entities and inefficient when deployed as a mining device.

Name: Tethys Beam
Description:
A mounted laser system specifically designed for the Nautilon Submarine.

Fires a concentrated plasma beam towards the intended target, which is then ignited. Such a trigger mechanism allows the use of high-energy optical mining systems in a liquid medium.

Name: Dredging Laser
Description:
Adds Terrain Manipulation capability to the laser systems of the Nautilon Submarine.

Cooled by specially designed water intakes, it is specifically calibrated to carve through the complex geology of the sea floor.

Name: High-power Sonar
Description:
A high-detail sonar device, capable of upgrading the scanner technology aboard a Nautilon-class submarine to Analysis Visor levels, pinning to the HUD all information typically revealed by the Analysis Visor.

Press SCAN to activate the High-Power Sonar.

Name: Environment Control Unit
Description:
This powerful environmental neutralising system is plugged directly into the pilot as they enter the cockpit. The system is powered via the Minotaur's main engine and requires no additional input. Some minor pain may be noticed around the insertion site.

Renders the Minotaur pilot impervious to all environmental hazards.

Name: Orbital Exocraft Materialiser
Description:
Construction allows the user to summon any owned Exocraft while in the same system as their freighter.

Interfaces with the Exosuit Quick Command Menu to ease of use.

Name: Orbital Exocraft Materialiser
Description:
Advanced integrated freighter equipment. Construction allows the user to summon any owned Exocraft while in the same system as their freighter. This module is placed as an entire room and comes with its functional units pre-installed.

Interfaces with the Exosuit Quick Command Menu for ease of use.

Name: Exocraft Specialist's Room
Description:
Integrated freighter research equipment tailored to the needs of exocraft technicians, and equipped with bespoke vehicular design software.

This module is placed as an entire room and comes with its functional units pre-installed.

Name: Nautilon Chamber
Description:
An advanced, fully-airlocked docking station for the Nautilon submarine.

The Nautilon Geobay must be constructed underwater.

Name: Nautilon Platform
Description:
An advanced, fully-watertight docking station for the Nautilon submarine.

This specially adapted platform is designed to be deployed on the surface of the water.

Name: Exocraft Summoning Station
Description:
Construction allows the user to summon any owned Exocraft from anywhere else in that system.

Interfaces with the Exosuit Quick Command Menu for ease of use. Can be compressed and carried within the Exosuit with DECONSTRUCT for later redeployment.

Name: Exocraft Terminal
Description: A research station tailored to the needs of Technicians, and equipped with bespoke vehicular design software.

Name: Exocraft Research Station
Description:
This self-sufficient portable research station allows access to a range of technology upgrades.

Deploy this station within a base to begin upgrade selection process.

Name: Utopia Exocraft Station
Description:
The Utopia Overseers wish for their brave settlers to be strong and well-equipped!

This officially-licensed portable research station allows access to a generous range of technology upgrades, easily purchased with the appropriate currency!

Construct and visit your own Utopia Exocraft Station today!
